Description: # concil
        
        concil is a simple container manager to run OCI-conform linux containers.
        
        It's aim is to run standalone applications in isolated environments in user space.
        
        Short comparision with Docker:
        
        |                      | Docker | Concil |
        |----------------------|:------:|:------:|
        |OCI-Repository        | ✓      | ✓      |
        |Signature             | ✓      | ✓      |
        |Encryption            | ✗      | ✓      |
        |Rootless / Daemonless | ✗      | ✓      |
        |Network isolation     | ✓      | ✗      |
        |Complexity            | high   | low    |
        
        
